DLG g

DLG 3
"""
{clr 2}{drws "younger person"}: What are you working on, Nonna?{/clr}
The summer was always hot. Even under the sun, it was humid. 
The smell of the sea lingered in the air as waves lapped against stone outside. 

I think it was calmer that day. 

I don't remember the waves. I remember Nonna better.
{clr 2}{drws "grandma"}: This will become a dress.{/clr}

In her hands, a needle and thread. Rested on her knees was the {wvy}cussinello{/wvy} and {wvy}murello{/wvy} with her work pinned on top.
{clr 2}{drws "younger person"}: Can I learn to make it too?{/clr}

{clr 2}{drws "grandma"}: Come here, bella, sit. I'll teach you.{/clr}
She said she'd show me. So I sat.
{exit "1" 13 13 "fade_b"}She let me practice alongside her, stitch by stitch.
"""
NAME grandma dialog

DLG 4
The door opens with a soft creak, already partly ajar.
NAME Door

DLG 5
{clr 2}{drws "cat"}: {wvy}Mrow?{/wvy}{/clr}{pg}Biscotto always kept Nonna company out of the heat.
NAME CatDialogueYay

DLG 6
I ask Nonna how much practice it takes to learn one stitch.{pg}I remember she told me it took a long time.{pg}It felt like a long time, as the sun moved in the sky and peeked inside the windows.
NAME Lace - Exit Narration One

DLG 7
One stitch, over and over, slowly it filled in the shape.
NAME exit narration 1

DLG 8
Every {wvy}greco{/wvy} stitch fills a little more space in the square.
NAME exit narration 2

DLG 9
You walk through the doorway
NAME exit narration 3

DLG a
Finally, {wvy}finally{/wvy}, I had finished a single square of lace{exit "7l" 15 0}
NAME Finished Lace

DLG b
"""
{
  - BridgeSeen == false ?
    {LandmarksSeen = LandmarksSeen + 1}{BridgeSeen = true}
  - else ?

}{wvy}Tre Pointi{/wvy}
Named for the three bridges here.
They connect three of the island's canals.
Colorful houses line all of the streets along the canals, reflected in the water. {
  - LandmarksSeen == 3 ?
    {pg}{exit "7n" 2 3 "fade_b"}The summers are still warm, and the waves still brush against the shoreline. The differences come with the passage of time, and my skills have grown as I have.
  - else ?
    {pg}
}
"""
NAME Bridge Map Icon dialog

DLG c
It takes much longer to make a small piece of lace than it does to walk the entire length of my home island, Burano.{exit "7m" 3 3}
NAME Exit to Map

DLG d
"""
{
  - SquareSeen == false ?
    {LandmarksSeen = LandmarksSeen + 1}{SquareSeen = true}
  - else ?

}{wvy}Piazza Baldassarre Galuppi{/wvy}
Named after the composer Baldassarre Galuppi, a statue of him lives in the square.
The {wvy}piazza{/wvy} is also home to the Burano War Memorial, and the Church of St. Martin Bishop.
The museum of Lace is also connected to the square.{
  - LandmarksSeen == 3 ?
    {pg}{exit "7n" 2 3 "fade_b"}The summers are still warm, and the waves still brush against the shoreline. The differences come with the passage of time, and my skills have grown as I have.
  - else ?
    {pg}
}
"""
NAME Square Icon dialog

DLG e
"""
{
  - MuseumSeen == false ?
    {LandmarksSeen = LandmarksSeen + 1}{MuseumSeen = true}
  - else ?

}{wvy}Il Museo del Merletto{/wvy}
The lace museum occupies the historic palace building where Burano's lace school used to teach the skills to people like my Nonna.{
  - LandmarksSeen == 3 ?
    {pg}{exit "7n" 2 3 "fade_b"}The summers are still warm, and the waves still brush against the shoreline. The differences come with the passage of time, and my skills have grown as I have.
  - else ?
    {pg}
}
"""
NAME Museum Map Icon dialog

DLG f
"""
{drws "younger person"}: "What are these?"{pg}I had asked, pointing at the lace pattern[{drwt "rosetti left side fix"}{drwt "rosetti"}{drwt "rosetti"}{drwt "rosetti"} ] I hadn't been taught to work on today.
{pg}{drws "grandma"}: Those are {wvy}rosetti{/wvy}, a different type of stitch than the one you practiced today.
"""
NAME Rosetti Question

DLG g
Now I carry on Nonna's lessons, making lace like she once did. And one day, I'll teach someone to carry it on too.{pg}{wvy}The End{/wvy}{end}
NAME ending 1

DLG h
The end
